&lt;h2 id="wrapping-up"&gt;Wrapping up
&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;p&gt;Hopefully this is useful. Note also that while this example is around the System Administrator Role you could use the same queries for other Roles as well. Sure beats clicking into a million screens in the PPAC.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;​&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Why can't I bulk close the incomplete activities on a Dynamics 365 Campaign Activity?</title><link>https://markjacobsen.net/2026/07/why-cant-i-bulk-close-the-incomplete-activities-on-a-dynamics-365-campaign-activity/</link><pubDate>Tue, 21 Jul 2026 17:21:26 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://markjacobsen.net/2026/07/why-cant-i-bulk-close-the-incomplete-activities-on-a-dynamics-365-campaign-activity/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Personally, I find it rather frustrating that you can&amp;rsquo;t bulk close open activities when viewing in a sub-grid under Campaign Activity. Ultimately it comes down to how things work behind the scenes since Campaign Activities can distribute multiple types of activities (phone calls, emails, etc). Additionally, the out-of-the-box command bar logic for activity status changes (like &amp;ldquo;Mark Complete&amp;rdquo; or &amp;ldquo;Close&amp;rdquo;) relies on record-type-specific logic which can often also prompt for record-type-specific data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;See also &lt;a class="link" href="https://share.gemini.google/PSJxwYoX8Y06" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
 &gt;https://share.gemini.google/PSJxwYoX8Y06&lt;/a&gt;​​​&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Visualize data with the new hierarchy control in D365</title><link>https://markjacobsen.net/2025/09/visualize-data-with-the-new-hierarchy-control-in-d365/</link><pubDate>Wed, 24 Sep 2025 11:51:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://markjacobsen.net/2025/09/visualize-data-with-the-new-hierarchy-control-in-d365/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Check out this article: &lt;a class="link" href="https://d365goddess.com/visualize-data-with-the-new-hierarchy-control/?utm_source=rss" target="_blank" rel="noopener"
 &gt;Visualize data with the new hierarchy control in D365&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This looks super cool and nice to see it being added (back) in as native functionality.&lt;/p&gt;
